pageContext.claim: “Outside of our country, they're calling me -- every country. They're calling me. So many countries. And I'm going to try and help them because we have thousands of ventilators being built. But nobody is asking for ventilators. Nobody is asking for beds because we built hospitals. I think we built 20,000 beds in a period of a couple of weeks.”
pageContext.analysis: The U.S. Defense Department reported building nearly 15,000 — not 20,000 — beds on April 8.
